                <head>289. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 10, 1962, Robert <persName corresp="#p_RKAG1">Gardiner</persName>
                    sent identical letters to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CA1"
                        >Adoula</persName> and Provincial President <persName corresp="#p_MT1"
                        >Tshombe</persName>, enclosing a “Programme for Implementation of the Plan
                    of National Reconciliation” and urging them to take the necessary actions with
                    the speed required to ensure its success. The program included steps to be taken
                    concerning the drafting of a new constitution, arrangements for allocation of
                    revenue and foreign exchange, currency unification, military unification,
                    consolidation of handling of foreign affairs under the central government, an
                    amnesty, cooperation with the United Nations, and reconstitution of the central
                    government with <gloss target="#Conakat1">Conakat</gloss> participation. For
                    text of the letter and its enclosure, see <hi rend="italic">American Foreign
                        Policy: Current Documents, 1962</hi>, pages 890–893.</p>
            </div>
